{"title_page": "Bruises (Lewis Capaldi song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Bruises\n| cover      = Lewis Capaldi - Bruises.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Lewis Capaldi]]\n| EP         = Bloom ''and the album'' [[Divinely Uninspired to a Hellish Extent]]\n| released   = 30 March 2017\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2016\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     = 3:38\n| label      = {{hlist|Self-released|[[Virgin Records|Virgin]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|Capaldi|James Earp}}\n| producer   =\n| next_title = [[Lost On You (Lewis Capaldi song)|Lost On You]]\n| next_year  = 2017\n}}\n\"'''Bruises'''\" is a song by Scottish singer-songwriter [[Lewis Capaldi]]. It was initially self-released independently on 31 March 2017, later being re-released as a digital download on 16 May 2017, after signing to [[Virgin Records]], as the lead single from his debut extended play ''Bloom'' and his debut studio album ''[[Divinely Uninspired to a Hellish Extent]]''.  <ref name=\"iTunes\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/bruises-single/1235575680|title=Bruises - Single by Lewis Capaldi|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=84znrPmOePc|title=Lewis Capaldi - Bruises (Audio)|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref> The song was re-released again on January 7, 2020 as his third US single.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download\n| title1  = Bruises\n| length1 = 3:38\n| title2  = Bruises\n| note2   = Steve Void remix\n| length2 = 3:32\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Remixes EP<ref name=\"remixes\"/>\n| title1  = Bruises\n| length1 = 3:38\n| title2  = Bruises\n| note2   = Live Orchestral version\n| length2 = 3:48\n| title3  = Bruises\n| note3   = Guitar acoustic\n| length3 = 3:46\n| title4  = Bruises\n| note4   = Steve Void remix\n| length4 = 3:32\n}}\n==Charts==\n===Wee